event: response.output_text.delta
data: {"type":"response.output_text.delta","content_index":0,"delta":".","item_id":"msg_0f3a9d0c8426acac0169e4506547d881958af5609143e6d1ba","logprobs":[],"obfuscation":"J1mFtomJKZozjYE","output_index":1,"sequence_number":402}

event: response.output_text.done
data: {"type":"response.output_text.done","content_index":0,"item_id":"msg_0f3a9d0c8426acac0169e4506547d881958af5609143e6d1ba","logprobs":[],"output_index":1,"sequence_number":403,"text":"To check whether **91** is prime, we test whether it has any divisors other than **1** and itself.\n\n### Step 1: Basic checks\n- **Not divisible by 2** (it’s odd).\n- **Not divisible by 3**:  \n  Sum of digits of 91 is \\(9+1=10\\). Since 10 isn’t divisible by 3, 91 isn’t divisible by 3.\n- **Not divisible by 5** (doesn’t end in 0 or 5).\n\n### Step 2: Only check primes up to \\(\\sqrt{91}\\)\nIf 91 were composite, it would have a factor less than or equal to \\(\\sqrt{91}\\).\n\\[\n\\sqrt{91} \\approx 9.54\n\\]\nSo we only need to check possible prime divisors \\(\\le 9.54\\), i.e.:\n\\[\n2,\\ 3,\\ 5,\\ 7\n\\]\nWe already ruled out \\(2,3,5\\).\n\n### Step 3: Test 7\n\\[\n91 \\div 7 = 13\n\\]\nAnd\n\\[\n7 \\times 13 = 91\n\\]\nSo 91 has a nontrivial divisor (7 and 13).\n\n### Conclusion\nSince **91 = 7 × 13**, it is **not prime**."}

event: response.content_part.done
data: {"type":"response.content_part.done","content_index":0,"item_id":"msg_0f3a9d0c8426acac0169e4506547d881958af5609143e6d1ba","output_index":1,"part":{"type":"output_text","annotations":[],"logprobs":[],"text":"To check whether **91** is prime, we test whether it has any divisors other than **1** and itself.\n\n### Step 1: Basic checks\n- **Not divisible by 2** (it’s odd).\n- **Not divisible by 3**:  \n  Sum of digits of 91 is \\(9+1=10\\). Since 10 isn’t divisible by 3, 91 isn’t divisible by 3.\n- **Not divisible by 5** (doesn’t end in 0 or 5).\n\n### Step 2: Only check primes up to \\(\\sqrt{91}\\)\nIf 91 were composite, it would have a factor less than or equal to \\(\\sqrt{91}\\).\n\\[\n\\sqrt{91} \\approx 9.54\n\\]\nSo we only need to check possible prime divisors \\(\\le 9.54\\), i.e.:\n\\[\n2,\\ 3,\\ 5,\\ 7\n\\]\nWe already ruled out \\(2,3,5\\).\n\n### Step 3: Test 7\n\\[\n91 \\div 7 = 13\n\\]\nAnd\n\\[\n7 \\times 13 = 91\n\\]\nSo 91 has a nontrivial divisor (7 and 13).\n\n### Conclusion\nSince **91 = 7 × 13**, it is **not prime**."},"sequence_number":404}

